## Fluxo de Movimentação de Estoque

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    actor Operador
    participant Scanner as Scanner Page
    participant DS as DataService
    participant API as PUT /products/:id/stock
    participant DB as PostgreSQL

    Operador->>Scanner: Escaneia código de barras
    Scanner->>DS: getProductByBarcode(barcode)
    DS->>API: GET /products/barcode/:barcode
    API->>DB: SELECT * FROM Product WHERE barcode = ?
    DB-->>API: Produto encontrado
    API-->>DS: Product JSON
    DS-->>Scanner: Exibe dados do produto

    Operador->>Scanner: Seleciona setor, qtd e confirma saída
    Scanner->>DS: updateStock(id, -qty, user, reason)
    DS->>API: PUT /products/:id/stock

    API->>DB: BEGIN TRANSACTION
    Note over API,DB: 1. Atualiza quantidade do produto
    Note over API,DB: 2. Cria StockMovement (SAIDA)
    Note over API,DB: 3. Cria AuditLog (MOVEMENT_OUT)
    API->>DB: COMMIT

    DB-->>API: OK
    API-->>DS: Produto atualizado
    DS-->>Scanner: Sucesso ✓
    Scanner-->>Operador: Exibe confirmação
```

---

## Fluxo de Autenticação

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    actor User as Usuário
    participant Login as Login Page
    participant Auth as AuthContext
    participant API as POST /api/auth/login
    participant DB as PostgreSQL

    User->>Login: Insere username + senha
    Login->>Auth: login(username, password)
    Auth->>API: POST { username, password }
    API->>DB: SELECT * FROM User WHERE username = ?
    DB-->>API: User record
    API->>API: bcrypt.compare(password, hash)
    API->>API: jwt.sign(payload, secret)
    API-->>Auth: { token, user }
    Auth->>Auth: Salva token no localStorage
    Auth-->>Login: Sucesso
    Login-->>User: Redireciona para Dashboard
```
